---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Navigation from '../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About pattaya.love — Who We Are"
  description="Meet the team behind pattaya.love — a mix of locals and expats who built this guide because we love Pattaya."
>
  <Navigation />

  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 bg-surface-card">
    <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Breadcrumb -->
      <nav class="text-sm text-ink-muted mb-8">
        <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
        <span class="mx-2">/</span>
        <span class="text-ink">About</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold font-headline tracking-tight text-ink mb-4">
        About pattaya.love
      </h1>
      <div class="h-1 w-16 bg-primary mt-2 mb-12 rounded-full"></div>

      <div class="editorial-content">
        <p class="text-lg text-ink-secondary leading-relaxed">
          We built pattaya.love because we love this city. Not the postcard version — the real one. The 3 AM street food, the quiet mornings on Wongamat Beach, the chaos of Songkran, and everything in between.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-headline text-ink mt-12 mb-4">Who We Are</h2>
        <p>
          pattaya.love is created by a mix of Thai locals and foreigners who live in or frequently visit Pattaya. Our contributors include long-term expats who have called the city home for years, Thai residents who know the places tourists never find, and regular visitors who keep coming back because nowhere else quite compares.
        </p>
        <p>
          We are not a travel agency. We are not sponsored by hotels or nightlife venues. We write about what we actually experience — the good, the honest, and the occasionally chaotic.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-headline text-ink mt-12 mb-4">What We Do</h2>
        <p>
          Every guide, review, and recommendation on this site comes from firsthand experience. We eat at the restaurants, stay at the hotels, visit the bars, and ride the baht buses. When we write that a hotel has great sea views or that a street food stall serves the best pad kra pao in Soi Buakhao, it is because we have been there ourselves.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our goal is simple: give visitors and expats the information they actually need, without the fluff and generic advice that plagues most travel sites. Pattaya is a unique city and it deserves a guide that reflects that.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-headline text-ink mt-12 mb-4">Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          Some links on this site are affiliate links. If you book a hotel or service through one of these links, we may earn a small commission at no extra cost to you. This helps us keep the site running and the content free. We only recommend places and services we would use ourselves. For more details, see our <a href="/affiliate-disclosure/">affiliate disclosure</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold font-headline text-ink mt-12 mb-4">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Got a tip, correction, or just want to say hi? Reach us at <a href="mailto:info@pattaya.love" class="text-primary hover:underline">info@pattaya.love</a> or join our <a href="https://www.facebook.com/groups/pattaya.love" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-primary hover:underline">Facebook community</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
